            <!-- figure out how include linking mechanism to link divs to bibl.  add a ref inside an ab inside the div-->
            <div type="edition" subtype="diplomatic" ana="b1" xml:lang="heb">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="edition" subtype="transcription" ana="b1" xml:lang="heb">
                <p>הדה נפשה דחנה<lb/>ברתה ד<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">חניא</supplied>ל כהנה<lb/>דמיתת יום שובתה<lb/>יומא טאבה קדמיה<lb/>דפסחה
                    חמשת עסר<lb/>יומין בירח ניסן<lb/>בשתה חמישיתה<lb/>דשאבועה דהי שנת<lb/>תלת מאה
                    ושתין<lb/>ותשע שנין לחרבן<lb/>בית מקדשה שלום<lb/>ניחא נפשה שלום</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" ana="b1">
                <p>This is the tombstone of Hannah<lb/>daughter of Ha[nie?]l the priest,<lb/>who
                    died on the Sabbath,<lb/>the first festival day<lb/>of Passover, on the
                    fifteenth<lb/>day of the month of Nisan,<lb/>in the fifth year<lb/>of the
                    sabbatical cycle, which is the year<lb/>three hundred and sixty<lb break="no"/>nine years
                    after the destruction<lb/>of the Temple. Peace.<lb/>May her soul rest,
                    Peace.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" ana="b1">
                <p>At Zoora, nfš (נפש) is the regular term for "tombstone," referring only to a
                    stone bearing an epitaph, not to an entire structure.<lb/>At Zoora, only one
                    woman out of all those known to us is mentioned along with her husband's name.
                    All the rest are mentioned with their fathers' names.</p>
            </div>
